{
  "texts": [
    "MTLoRA with different decodersWe analyze the effect of using different decoders on the performance of MTLoRA.",
    "We choose 3 commonly used decoders for dense prediction tasks: (1) HRNet [33], which interpolates and concatenates multi-scale features from the hierarchical backbone and then passes them to a couple of MLP layers.",
    "(2) SegFormer [35], which uses MLP layers to combine the multi-scale features from the hierarchical backbone, then parse them to one last MLP layer for prediction.",
    "(3) Atrous Spatial Pyramid Pooling (ASPP) [3], which has a more complicated architecture utilizing spatial pyramid pooling capable of extracting multi-scale contextual information by probing the incoming features with filters or pooling operations at multiple rates and multiple effective fields-of-view.",
    "We plug those decoders into a pretrained Swin-Tiny backbone, then use our MTLoRA technique to train the model to perform multiple downstream tasks."
  ]
}